LogFile.FinalText: In a lot of homes you find a pet, and most people prefer either a dog or a cat. So far the soft puppy beats the sweet kitten in the contest about being the most popular pet in Denmark. While the dog's loyality may be contributing factor for its large popularity, the numerous cat owners love the cat's independence. While the conventional cat owner believes that a dog is too independent and dirty, the many dog owners see cats as lazy and impersonal. Many pet owners chose a pet, which reflects their own personality. When the big strong man buys a large strong dog, the personality of the dog enhances the ego of the dog owner. In contrast to this the femine woman often prefers the beautiful and elegant cat. Dogs and cats normally get along fine, if they are used to each other. However, often the dog owner and the cat owner seem to disagree more than the dog and the cat.
